Title: Lorentz Invariant Renormalization in Causal Perturbation Theory
Authors: K. Bresser, G. Pinter and D. Prange
Comments: 9 pages, no figures
\\
  In the framework of causal perturbation theory renormalization consists of
the extension of distributions. We give the explicit form of a Lorentz
invariant extension of a scalar distribution, depending on one difference of
space time coordinates.
